    {
      "title": "The Expedition of Tabuk",
      "subtitle": "When Abu Bakr (RA) Gave Everything He Owned",
      "intro": "During the 9th year after Hijrah, the Muslim community in Madinah faced the threat of a Roman attack. The Prophet Muhammad ﷺ called the believers to prepare for the expedition to Tabuk — a long and exhausting journey through extreme heat and shortage of supplies. What happened next became one of the greatest examples of sacrifice, faith, and loyalty in Islamic history.",
      "sections": [
        {
          "isBullets": false,
          "heading": "The Call to Sacrifice",
          "paragraphs": [
            "Word reached Madinah that the Roman Empire was preparing to confront the Muslims. In response, the Prophet Muhammad ﷺ called the believers to join an expedition to Tabuk, a location far to the north.",
            "This was during intense desert heat and a time of limited resources. It became known as 'The Year of Hardship' because many companions struggled just to survive, let alone fund a military campaign.",
            "The Prophet ﷺ stood before the companions and urged them to donate whatever they could — wealth, supplies, animals — to support the army of Islam."
          ]
        },
        {
          "isBullets": false,
          "heading": "Umar’s Generosity",
          "paragraphs": [
            "Umar ibn al-Khattab (RA) saw this as a moment to serve Allah with true sacrifice — and, in his heart, to finally match or surpass Abu Bakr (RA) in charity.",
            "He gathered half of everything he owned and brought it to the Prophet ﷺ. When the Prophet ﷺ asked him, 'What have you left for your family?', Umar (RA) replied, 'Half, O Messenger of Allah.'",
            "It was a moment of sincere giving. Umar (RA) felt certain he had done something truly great that day."
          ]
        },
        {
          "isBullets": false,
          "heading": "Abu Bakr’s Sacrifice",
          "paragraphs": [
            "Then Abu Bakr as-Siddiq (RA) arrived.",
            "He did not bring half. He brought all of his wealth — every coin, everything he possessed.",
            "The Prophet ﷺ asked him, with love, 'O Abu Bakr, what have you left for your family?'",
            "Abu Bakr (RA) answered, 'I left Allah and His Messenger for them.'",
            "This was not recklessness. It was absolute trust. Abu Bakr (RA) believed that relying on Allah and supporting the Messenger ﷺ was a greater protection and provision for his family than any amount of money."
          ]
        },
        {
          "isBullets": false,
          "heading": "The Prophet’s Testimony",
          "paragraphs": [
            "The Prophet ﷺ later said: 'There is no one who has done more favor to me with his wealth and his companionship than Abu Bakr ibn Abi Quhafa.' (Tirmidhi)",
            "This statement shows two things: Abu Bakr (RA) gave not only money, but unwavering loyalty. He stood with the Prophet ﷺ in every moment, in ease and in hardship.",
            "His sacrifice at Tabuk became a proof of his rank in this ummah."
          ]
        },
        {
          "isBullets": true,
          "heading": "Lessons from the Story",
          "paragraphs": [
            "True Sacrifice: Real charity is not just giving what is easy to give — it’s giving while trusting Allah with what comes next.",
            "Faith Over Wealth: Abu Bakr (RA) showed that the greatest security for a family is faith, not possessions.",
            "Competing in Goodness: Umar (RA) brought half, Abu Bakr (RA) brought all. Both competed to please Allah, and both were honored. Islam encourages believers to inspire each other in doing good."
          ]
        },
        {
          "isBullets": false,
          "heading": "Legacy",
          "paragraphs": [
            "The Expedition of Tabuk tested the strength and unity of the Muslims. Despite the harsh heat, long distance, and lack of supplies, the believers responded with loyalty and sacrifice.",
            "The story of Abu Bakr (RA) giving everything he owned became one of the most powerful examples of pure sincerity for the sake of Allah.",
            "To this day, his answer — 'I left Allah and His Messenger for them' — is remembered as a model of what it means to love Allah above the dunya."
          ]
        }
      ]
